<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9355554-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s13110"><num value="13110">§ 13110.</num><heading> Authority of Comptroller General</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idb9355555-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s13110/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Access to Financial Disclosure Reports</inline>.—</heading><content>The Comptroller General shall have access to financial disclosure reports filed under this subchapter for the purposes of carrying out the Comptroller General’s statutory responsibilities.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idb9355556-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s13110/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Studies</inline>.—</heading><content>Not later than <date date="1992-12-31">December 31, 1992</date>, and regularly thereafter, the Comptroller General shall conduct a study to determine whether the provisions of this subchapter are being carried out effectively.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idb9355557-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/286/s3/c">Pub. L. 117–286, § 3(c)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4295">136 Stat. 4295</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
